---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About One Page of Thought and the gentle editorial mood behind the site." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About</h1>
			<p>
				One Page of Thought is a quiet corner for everyday technology, small questions, and ideas that are
				better explained gently. It is meant to feel less like a crowded feed and more like a single clear
				page you can return to when you want something understandable.
			</p>
			<p>
				Some pieces explain simple concepts, some compare tools, and some help with ordinary digital decisions.
				The common thread is calm writing, light structure, and the feeling that even a confusing topic can be
				made softer around the edges.
			</p>
			<p>
				If the site does its job well, each page should feel like one small thought held still long enough to
				be useful.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
